Now I can see the issue. Look at line 25-36 of queryCode.tmpl for the `:one` case:

```go
func (q *Queries) {{.MethodName}}(ctx context.Context, {{ dbarg }} {{.Arg.Pair}}) ({{.Ret.DefineType}}, error) {
    {{- template "queryCodeStdExec" . }}
    {{- if or (ne .Arg.Pair .Ret.Pair) (ne .Arg.DefineType .Ret.DefineType) }}
    var {{.Ret.Name}} {{.Ret.Type}}
    {{- end}}
    err := row.Scan({{.Ret.Scan}})
    ...
    return {{.Ret.ReturnName}}, err
}
```

The `var {{.Ret.Name}}` declaration is only emitted when the arg and ret pairs differ OR their define types differ. When both the arg and ret have the same name and same type, the variable declaration is skipped, and `row.Scan` writes into the arg variable. Let me look at the `QueryValue` type to understand `Pair`, `DefineType`, `Name`, etc

